SUMMARY:Merrily We Roll Along
DESCRIPTION:Music and lyrics by Stephen Sondheim  Book by George Furth  B
 ased on the original play by George S. Kaufman and Moss Hart  Directed by
  Richard Roland  Musical Direction by Ray Fellman  Choreographed by DJ Gr
 ay    Sondheim's semi-autobiographical musical turns back the clock on fr
 iendship and the high price of success. Merrily We Roll Along begins in t
 he present and moves backwards\, tracing the lives of a wealthy\, jaded c
 omposer and his two estranged friends through each milestone of their per
 sonal and professional lives.      &#160\;  Running Time: There will be a
  15 minute intermission
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p class="title small">  Music and lyrics by
  Stephen Sondheim</p><p class="title small">  Book by George Furth</p><p 
 class="title small">  Based on the original play by George S. Kaufman and
  Moss Hart</p><p class="title small">  Directed by Richard Roland</p><p c
 lass="title small">  Musical Direction by Ray Fellman</p><p class="title 
 small">  Choreographed by DJ Gray</p><div class="synopsis"><p>    Sondhei
 m's semi-autobiographical musical turns back the clock on friendship and 
 the high price of success. <em>Merrily We Roll Along</em> begins in the p
 resent and moves backwards\, tracing the lives of a wealthy\, jaded compo
 ser and his two estranged friends through each milestone of their persona
 l and professional lives.  </p><p>    &#160\;  </p><p><strong>Running Tim
 e</strong>: There will be a 15 minute intermission  </p></div>
